The paper discusses metaheuristics, which are optimization algorithms used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the No Free Lunch Theorems, which are relevant to the design and analysis of algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the practical considerations of when to ignore these theorems, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
